00:32.195 --> 00:35.632
<i>There's a moment of orderly
silence before a football play begins.</i>

00:36.033 --> 00:40.333
<i>Players are in position, linemen
are frozen, and anything is possible.</i>

00:40.504 --> 00:43.564
<i>Almost Indian-summer
weather here in mid-November.</i>

00:45.209 --> 00:50.112
<i>Then, like a traffic accident,
stuff begins to randomly collide.</i>

00:50.281 --> 00:53.045
<i>From the snap of the ball
to the snap of the first bone...</i>

00:53.217 --> 00:55.947
<i>...is closer to four seconds than five.</i>

00:56.120 --> 00:59.021
<i>First and 10.
Riggins, flea flicker back to Theismann.</i>

00:59.190 --> 01:01.090
<i>Theismann's in a lot of trouble.</i>

01:04.128 --> 01:07.393
<i>One Mississippi.
Joe Theismann, the Redskins' quarterback...</i>

01:07.565 --> 01:10.033
<i>...takes the snap and hands off
to his running back.</i>

01:10.201 --> 01:11.532
<i>First and 10. Riggins-</i>

01:11.702 --> 01:13.294
<i>Two Mississippi.</i>

01:13.471 --> 01:15.632
<i>It's a trick play, a flea flicker...</i>

01:15.806 --> 01:18.741
<i>...and the running back tosses the ball
back to the quarterback.</i>

01:18.909 --> 01:21.241
<i>Flea flicker back to Theismann.</i>

01:21.712 --> 01:22.838
<i>Three Mississippi.</i>

01:23.014 --> 01:27.041
<i>Up to now, the play's been defined
by what the quarterback sees.</i>

01:27.218 --> 01:30.619
<i>It’s about to be defined
by what he doesn't.</i>

01:31.389 --> 01:32.720
<i>Four Mississippi.</i>

01:32.890 --> 01:36.519
<i>Lawrence Taylor is the best
defensive player in the NFL...</i>

01:36.694 --> 01:40.061
<i>...and has been from the time he
stepped onto the field as a rookie.</i>

01:40.231 --> 01:42.028
<i>Theismann's in a lot of trouble.</i>

01:42.199 --> 01:43.723
<i>And it was Lawrence Taylor...</i>

01:43.901 --> 01:48.099
<i>...who slammed Theismann to the ground
at the 42-yard line. The blitz was on...</i>

01:48.272 --> 01:51.571
<i>He will also change
the game of football as we know it.</i>

01:51.742 --> 01:54.267
<i>We'll look at it with
the reverse angle one more time.</i>

01:54.445 --> 01:57.312
<i>And I suggest if your stomach is weak,
you just don't watch.</i>

01:57.481 --> 01:59.540
<i>Legendary quarterback Joe Theismann...</i>

01:59.717 --> 02:02.185
<i>...never played another down of football.</i>

02:04.355 --> 02:06.687
<i>Now, y'all would guess that,
more often than not...</i>

02:06.857 --> 02:10.156
<i>...the highest paid player
on an NFL team is a quarterback...</i>

02:10.328 --> 02:11.818
<i>...and you'd be right.</i>

02:11.996 --> 02:14.726
<i>But what you probably don't know
is, more often than not...</i>

02:14.899 --> 02:19.598
<i>...the second highest paid player is,
thanks to Lawrence Taylor, a left tackle.</i>

02:19.770 --> 02:23.706
<i>Because as every housewife knows, the
first check you write is for the mortgage...</i>

02:23.874 --> 02:26.365
<i>...but the second is for the insurance.</i>

02:26.544 --> 02:31.106
<i>And the left tackle's job is to protect the
quarterback from what he can't see coming.</i>

02:31.282 --> 02:33.045
<i>To protect his blind side.</i>

02:33.284 --> 02:37.050
<i>The ideal left tackle is big,
but a lot of people are big.</i>

02:37.221 --> 02:40.190
<i>He's wide in the butt
and massive in the thighs.</i>

02:40.358 --> 02:44.454
<i>He has long arms, giant hands
and feet as quick as a hiccup.</i>

02:46.630 --> 02:49.155
<i>This is a rare and expensive
combination...</i>

02:49.333 --> 02:54.066
<i>...the need for which can be traced to that
Monday night game and Lawrence Taylor.</i>

02:54.238 --> 02:58.868
<i>For on that day, he not only
altered Joe Theismann's life...</i>

02:59.043 --> 03:00.442
<i>...but mine as well.</i>

03:06.951 --> 03:08.816
Mr. Oher.

03:08.986 --> 03:10.920
Mr. Oher.

03:11.122 --> 03:13.955
Do you understand?
Do you know why I'm here?

03:15.092 --> 03:16.855
To investigate?

03:17.027 --> 03:18.654
Yes. To investigate.

03:20.531 --> 03:24.433
I'm here to investigate
your odd... predicament.

03:25.035 --> 03:28.061
Do you find it odd, your predicament?

03:29.774 --> 03:31.469
Michael?

03:32.109 --> 03:34.009
I don't know.

03:35.045 --> 03:38.481
- Can I-? Can I leave now?
- No, you can’t.

05:33.430 --> 05:35.728
Where's Coach Cotton's office?

05:36.367 --> 05:38.130
Thanks, man.

05:47.978 --> 05:49.878
They said you were the coach.

05:50.614 --> 05:51.911
Bert Cotton.

05:52.783 --> 05:56.241
Tony Hamilton, but everybody
just calls me Big Tony.

06:00.591 --> 06:03.116
Hey, Big Mike, check it out.

06:05.129 --> 06:07.222
Not even locked.

06:08.198 --> 06:10.632
White people are crazy.

06:14.438 --> 06:16.838
<i>I promised my ma, Boo,
on her deathbed...</i>

06:17.007 --> 06:20.670
...that I'd get my son, Steven, out of
public school and into a church school.

06:20.844 --> 06:25.247
I appreciate that, Tony,
but I'm not involved with admissions.

06:25.416 --> 06:27.907
I just figured maybe
I can come talk to you...

06:28.085 --> 06:30.553
...seeing as though
you might need some players.

06:31.322 --> 06:35.918
- What kind of sport does he play?
- Anything with a ball. The boy's good too.

06:36.093 --> 06:38.926
Classes start in a week.
It'd have to be for next semester.

06:40.331 --> 06:41.958
I know what you're thinking, coach.

06:42.366 --> 06:45.267
But look here, I got money, all right?

06:45.436 --> 06:48.530
See, I'm a mechanic at Wilson’s Auto,
the other side of town.

06:48.872 --> 06:53.605
Well, look, what if somebody drops out
or moves? Could they get in then?

06:54.445 --> 06:56.811
"They"? You only mentioned one son.

06:56.981 --> 07:00.109
That’s right, Steven.
But there's another boy.

07:00.451 --> 07:03.784
- Heh. Another boy?
- Yeah.

07:06.824 --> 07:10.282
Big Mike. Sleeps on my couch
from time to time.

07:10.461 --> 07:13.021
It's a bad deal. You know,
his mom's on that crack pipe.

07:13.197 --> 07:16.655
He ain't got nobody else. He just
wanted to come along for the ride.

07:17.034 --> 07:18.695
- They're here?
- Yeah.

07:19.737 --> 07:23.173
Now, the little one, that’s Steven...

07:23.340 --> 07:24.932
...and the big one...

07:25.109 --> 07:26.201
Big Mike.

07:35.252 --> 07:36.844
Swish!

07:39.356 --> 07:41.381
Big Mike! Ha-ha.

07:43.193 --> 07:44.626
Come on.

07:51.502 --> 07:53.094
Mother of God.

07:54.571 --> 07:57.540
<i>Steven Hamilton's paperwork
looks acceptable to me...</i>

07:57.708 --> 08:00.939
...and I believe he'll do fine.
But this other kid...

08:01.111 --> 08:03.170
- Big Mike.
- Michael Oher...

08:03.347 --> 08:05.781
...gives us no reason to believe that...

08:05.949 --> 08:09.316
...based on his records,
that he would be successful here.

08:09.486 --> 08:10.680
Well, how bad could it be?

08:10.854 --> 08:14.381
We're not exactly sure how old he is,
due to his lack of records.

08:14.558 --> 08:17.550
He has a measured IQ of 80,
which is sixth percentile.

08:18.128 --> 08:22.394
His grade-point average
begins with zero, 0.6.

08:22.566 --> 08:24.500
Everyone passed him along.

08:24.668 --> 08:28.104
They gave him D's so they could
hand their problem off to the next school.

08:30.074 --> 08:31.405
He's a brave kid.

08:34.178 --> 08:38.706
For wanting to come here,
for wanting a quality education.

08:38.881 --> 08:43.376
An education denied him by
the poor quality of schools he's attended.

08:43.554 --> 08:47.354
Most kids with his background wouldn’t
come within 200 miles of this place.

08:47.524 --> 08:52.484
Coach Cotton, we understand your interest
in this young man’s athletic abilities.

08:52.663 --> 08:55.632
He wouldn’t be able to play sports
until he got his grades up.

08:55.799 --> 08:57.892
Forget sports.

08:58.102 --> 08:59.592
Look at the wall.

08:59.770 --> 09:03.968
"Christian." We either take that
seriously or we paint over it.

09:04.875 --> 09:08.276
You don't admit Michael Oher
because of sports.

09:08.445 --> 09:11.505
You admit him because
it's the right thing to do.

09:56.994 --> 09:58.655
Class, this is Mike Oher...

09:58.829 --> 10:02.458
...and he's new here so I expect
you all to make him feel welcome.

10:02.633 --> 10:04.828
Mike, just take any empty seat.

10:08.338 --> 10:11.398
This is a quiz based on the information...

10:11.575 --> 10:15.067
...you learned last year
in your science curriculum.

10:15.245 --> 10:18.009
Don't worry, it's not gonna be graded.

10:18.182 --> 10:20.912
I just wanna see how much information
we need to hit again.

10:21.084 --> 10:23.416
Just answer whatever you know.

10:55.786 --> 10:58.050
Thank you.

11:14.638 --> 11:18.199
- Can I leave now?
- Yeah.

11:22.179 --> 11:23.441
Take your book.

11:41.899 --> 11:43.992
I'm tired
of having someone always in our home.

11:44.167 --> 11:45.930
I'm tired of him eating all the food.

11:46.103 --> 11:48.537
Look, man, you gotta be Christian
about this thing.

11:48.705 --> 11:50.900
Let somebody else
be Christian about this thing.

11:51.074 --> 11:54.271
Dee, come on, I can’t kick him out
on the street like he's some dog.

11:54.444 --> 11:56.344
Let somebody else
take the responsibility.

11:56.513 --> 11:59.141
What, you want me to go to
Beale Street and drop him off?

11:59.316 --> 12:01.307
When do I have time
just to be with you?

12:01.485 --> 12:06.218
All right, all right. Whatever.
You win. I'll take care of it.

12:10.727 --> 12:13.161
I don't care if Patrick Ramsey
approved the chair.

12:13.330 --> 12:16.766
He's an NFL quarterback,
not Martha fricking Stewart.

12:16.967 --> 12:21.097
Because there is a difference
between Bunny Williams and a La-Z-Boy.

12:21.271 --> 12:23.762
<i>No, see, when MTV Cribs
comes to his house...</i>

12:23.941 --> 12:25.806
...he’ll be showing off
his home theater.

12:25.976 --> 12:28.501
All I'm gonna see
is a brown Barcalounger.

12:28.679 --> 12:31.307
No, listen to me, I'm the designer,
my name is on it.

12:31.481 --> 12:34.678
Deliver what I ordered, all right?
Thank you.

12:43.994 --> 12:45.052
Yeah!

12:48.432 --> 12:51.026
What’d I miss?
- Collins just got a dig.

12:51.201 --> 12:53.829
It's girls' volleyball, Mom.
You didn't miss anything.

12:56.740 --> 12:57.866
Oh!

12:58.041 --> 13:00.976
- Come on, Collins, move your feet.
Good job, Collins.

13:01.144 --> 13:02.236
Go.

13:06.283 --> 13:07.545
We'll wait for you outside.

13:07.718 --> 13:10.278
Don't double condition in
the shower, you have homework.

13:10.454 --> 13:11.921
I'm going to Cannon’s to study.

13:12.089 --> 13:17.550
SJ! SJ, do not go in the girls' locker
room again. Come here! SJ, come here!

13:30.340 --> 13:33.275
<i>The big kid's been here
for, what, a month?</i>

13:33.677 --> 13:35.577
He's still not cutting it in my class.

13:35.746 --> 13:39.443
Why does Admissions do this?
I mean, it's not fair to us or the boy.

13:39.616 --> 13:41.277
They're just setting him up to fail.

13:41.451 --> 13:43.783
I don't think he has any idea
of what I'm teaching.

13:43.954 --> 13:46.445
And how would you know if he did?
He won't even talk.

13:47.424 --> 13:48.448
He writes.

13:48.625 --> 13:50.525
His name. Barely.

13:51.695 --> 13:54.255
He threw this in the trash can.

13:57.968 --> 14:00.801
"I look and I see white everywhere:

14:00.971 --> 14:06.136
White walls, white floors,
and a lot of white people.

14:06.476 --> 14:11.743
The teachers do not know I have no idea
of anything they are talking about.

14:11.915 --> 14:14.975
I do not wanna listen to anyone,
especially the teachers.

14:15.152 --> 14:20.112
They are giving homework and expecting
me to do the problems on my own.

14:20.490 --> 14:22.890
I have never done homework in my life.

14:23.693 --> 14:28.460
I go to the bathroom,
look in the mirror and say:

14:28.765 --> 14:30.460
"This is not Michael Oher."

14:35.338 --> 14:37.431
He entitled it "White Walls."

14:37.707 --> 14:39.572
How's the spelling?

14:51.488 --> 14:52.955
Hi.

15:00.363 --> 15:03.924
Smile at them.
It lets them know you're their friend.

15:08.872 --> 15:10.567
You're Big Mike, right?

15:11.808 --> 15:12.968
Well, I'm Sean.

15:13.143 --> 15:17.944
But everyone calls me SJ. It's for
Sean Junior. My father's name is Sean.

15:18.115 --> 15:22.017
Sean Tuohy? He was a basketball star
at Ole Miss, point guard.

15:22.185 --> 15:24.119
Now he owns like a million Taco Bells.

15:34.731 --> 15:36.562
Who is that, SJ?
Big Mike.

15:38.468 --> 15:40.561
Get your feet off my dash.

15:41.638 --> 15:43.037
Thank you. Put on your seat belt.

15:51.982 --> 15:53.677
Big Mike?

15:56.553 --> 16:00.751
Mike, I got a call from someone
at the police department.

16:04.628 --> 16:10.692
You remember a story in the papers
a while back about a man who...

16:10.901 --> 16:13.335
...fell off an overpass?

16:13.503 --> 16:15.698
No one knew who he was.

16:15.872 --> 16:20.673
They didn't know if he jumped or if...

16:21.711 --> 16:25.909
Well, anyway, he- He passed away.

16:29.252 --> 16:31.982
Mike, that man was your father.

16:35.258 --> 16:38.159
They've been looking for
somebody to notify and they-

16:38.328 --> 16:41.456
They found your name in our registry.

16:43.366 --> 16:45.926
I'm really sorry, son.

16:51.041 --> 16:53.032
Were you close to him?

16:57.414 --> 17:00.076
When's the last time you saw him?

17:05.255 --> 17:07.314
I don't know.

18:39.983 --> 18:42.713
- He knows it!
- Who knows it and what does he know?

18:42.986 --> 18:46.513
The material. Michael Oher.
I gave him this test verbally.

18:46.690 --> 18:50.057
- Is that even allowed?
- A "C"? On how big a curve?

18:50.226 --> 18:53.127
He's been listening all along.
It's amazing what he's absorbed.

18:53.296 --> 18:57.357
And, trust me, he's listening to you too.
Now, his reading level is low...

18:57.534 --> 19:01.026
...and he's got no idea
how to learn in a classroom...

19:01.204 --> 19:06.107
I'm not saying he's gonna pass,
but Big Mike is not stupid.

19:06.276 --> 19:08.574
Hey. Good job.
Mama. Daddy.

19:08.745 --> 19:10.762
Good job.
Hey I got a question for you.

19:10.812 --> 19:11.403
Yeah?

19:11.581 --> 19:15.312
There was a little girl about two rows
back. What was her name?

19:15.485 --> 19:17.680
- Oh, that was Kinsey.
- Kinsey, yeah.

19:17.854 --> 19:20.322
I saw your little Indian feathers
get all ruffled up.

19:20.490 --> 19:21.684
Yeah! She is nice.

19:21.858 --> 19:23.826
SJ. Don't let this go to your head...

19:23.993 --> 19:26.791
...but I thought you were
very convincing in the role of...

19:26.963 --> 19:28.794
- Indian Number 3?
- Yes.

19:28.965 --> 19:32.366
I tried out for the chief,
but they gave it to Andy Sung.

19:32.535 --> 19:36.596
I can’t be sure, but I think there's
some multi-cultural-bias thing working.

19:36.773 --> 19:39.469
Or maybe they just thought
that he'd make a better chief.

19:39.642 --> 19:41.439
Dad, he's, like, Chinese.

19:41.611 --> 19:43.010
Yeah, and you're Irish.

19:43.179 --> 19:45.739
If you weren't the chief,
how did you get the headdress?

19:45.915 --> 19:49.146
Dad, I'm gonna need a few more
of those free quesadilla tickets.

19:51.621 --> 19:53.851
And where does the acorn fall?

19:54.023 --> 19:57.015
Hey, don't laugh too hard.
The quesadillas saved our ass.

19:57.193 --> 19:58.785
Don't use the A-word.

20:04.734 --> 20:05.996
What is he wearing?

20:07.570 --> 20:09.435
It's freezing.

20:09.606 --> 20:12.040
- What's his name again?
- Big Mike.

20:12.942 --> 20:15.172
Where is he going?

20:16.279 --> 20:19.407
Hey, Big Mike. Where you headed?

20:19.582 --> 20:20.606
Gym.

20:21.384 --> 20:22.408
Go ahead.

20:34.597 --> 20:35.689
Turn around.

20:43.273 --> 20:44.467
Big Mike!

20:44.641 --> 20:46.506
Stop the car.

20:50.447 --> 20:51.539
Big Mike.

20:52.449 --> 20:55.009
Hey. My name's Leigh Anne Tuohy.
My kids go to Wingate.

20:55.185 --> 20:56.812
You said you were going to the gym?

20:58.354 --> 20:59.844
School gym's closed.

21:00.356 --> 21:01.948
Why were you going to the gym?

21:03.960 --> 21:06.394
Big Mike, why were you
going to the gym?

21:07.730 --> 21:09.698
Because it's- It's warm.

21:11.201 --> 21:12.998
Do you have anyplace to stay tonight?

21:14.904 --> 21:16.201
Don't you dare lie to me.

21:29.152 --> 21:33.248
I've seen that look many times.
She's about to get her way.

21:34.190 --> 21:35.248
Come on.

21:37.694 --> 21:39.127
Come on.

21:42.332 --> 21:44.266
SJ, make room.

21:44.434 --> 21:46.095
Get inside.

21:47.804 --> 21:49.294
Come on.

22:00.783 --> 22:03.115
- Where we going?
- Home.

22:18.301 --> 22:22.863
I know, it's my favorite part.
He's so cute.

22:23.306 --> 22:25.399
How'd the dork do in the school play?

22:30.013 --> 22:31.310
Um...

22:31.481 --> 22:32.641
Okay.

22:33.082 --> 22:36.074
Collins, do you know Big Mike
from school?

22:37.587 --> 22:41.284
I'd give you the guest bedroom,
but it's full of sample boxes.

22:41.457 --> 22:44.756
And the sectional in the family room
slides apart when you sleep on it.

22:44.928 --> 22:47.123
Least that’s what Sean says.

22:47.297 --> 22:49.060
Mr. Tuohy sleeps on the couch?

22:49.332 --> 22:50.924
Only when he's bad. All right.

22:51.100 --> 22:55.469
The powder room is right there and we
will be upstairs if you need us. All right?

22:56.172 --> 22:59.266
Okay. Sleep tight, honey.

23:52.562 --> 23:54.052
<i>Was this a bad idea?</i>

23:54.330 --> 23:55.354
What?

23:55.531 --> 23:58.967
Don't lie there and pretend like you're
not thinking the same thing as me.

23:59.135 --> 24:02.627
Tell me what you're thinking so I'll know
what's supposed to be on my mind.

24:02.805 --> 24:04.932
How well do you know Big Mike?

24:05.108 --> 24:07.576
Case you hadn't noticed,
he didn't have much to say.

24:07.744 --> 24:10.304
What's the big deal?
It's just for one night, right?

24:12.215 --> 24:14.809
It is just for one night,
right, Leigh Anne?

24:17.420 --> 24:19.820
You don't think he'll steal anything,
do you?

24:20.957 --> 24:23.425
I guess we'll know in the morning.

24:35.538 --> 24:37.506
<i>...talking about Mississippi and Arkansas.</i>

24:37.674 --> 24:39.141
<i>The fight's gotten more interesting.</i>

24:39.308 --> 24:42.675
Well, if you hear a scream,
call the insurance adjuster.

25:02.131 --> 25:03.860
Mike?

25:13.209 --> 25:15.370
Big Mike?

25:15.912 --> 25:17.675
Mike?

25:30.626 --> 25:32.457
Big Mike!

25:40.570 --> 25:42.299
You gonna make me
walk the whole way?

25:43.072 --> 25:45.063
All right, then.

25:45.575 --> 25:46.974
Where are you going?

25:47.877 --> 25:48.901
I don't know.

25:49.479 --> 25:53.609
Well, are you spending Thanksgiving
with your family?

25:53.916 --> 25:56.612
<i>Those 40, 50 guys
from State here can quiet them down.</i>

25:56.786 --> 25:59.220
<i>As you mentioned,
the Mississippi State defensive-</i>

25:59.388 --> 26:01.253
- Come and get it, y'all.
- Yeah, baby!

26:01.424 --> 26:03.016
Let's eat!

26:03.359 --> 26:04.656
Come on!

26:05.495 --> 26:06.553
It's that Rebel turkey.

26:07.497 --> 26:10.330
Thank your mother for driving
to the store and getting this.

26:10.500 --> 26:12.161
Thank you, Mama.
- Thank you, Mama.

26:12.335 --> 26:15.270
Food and football.
Eat all you want.

26:15.438 --> 26:18.498
Come on. Hustle, hustle.
We gotta get back over there.

26:18.674 --> 26:20.369
Going, Dad.

26:20.810 --> 26:22.175
Don't take my spot.

26:22.345 --> 26:24.813
- No rushing, SJ. SJ, slow down.
- Coming through.

26:24.981 --> 26:28.473
No.
This is fantastic.

26:29.652 --> 26:33.679
Oh, y’all, I forgot
the potato salad. How's Ole Miss doing?

26:33.856 --> 26:36.347
They're kicking butt.

26:36.993 --> 26:39.052
<i>One wide receiver left...
Good, huh?</i>

26:39.228 --> 26:42.288
<i>...and one corner, number 30,
out in press coverage-</i>

26:42.465 --> 26:44.490
Sean, salad.

26:45.635 --> 26:47.500
It's great, Mom.
So good. Thanks, Mama.

26:47.670 --> 26:48.762
Yeah, Mama.

26:48.938 --> 26:51.998
<i>Nice little surge,
but not much running inside.</i>

26:52.175 --> 26:54.541
<i>Come on.
- And the Rebels got third and long here.</i>

26:54.710 --> 26:58.237
<i>Birdsong and Mawhinney on the tackle.
Ole Miss, five of 10 on third downs.</i>

26:58.414 --> 27:01.076
<i>From the 26, third down and six
for the Rebs here.</i>

27:01.250 --> 27:02.274
Come on, defense.

27:02.451 --> 27:05.579
<i>I formation. The rain is slow,
let's see if they try a pass or not.</i>

27:05.755 --> 27:08.155
<i>Now Turner goes in motion
out of the backfield.</i>

27:08.324 --> 27:10.087
<i>State showing blitz, Manning to throw.</i>

27:10.259 --> 27:13.558
<i>Runs to his right,
throws it at the feet of the-</i>

27:13.729 --> 27:15.424
- Hey. Mom.
- What?

27:15.598 --> 27:17.429
But it's Thanksgiving.

27:19.235 --> 27:22.329
- Wow.
- Why are we eating in here?

27:29.579 --> 27:30.944
Shall we say grace?

27:48.598 --> 27:53.865
Heavenly Father, we thank you for
all the many blessings on this family.

27:54.036 --> 27:56.698
We thank you for bringing us
a new friend.

27:57.373 --> 28:00.536
And we ask that you look after us
on this holiday season...

28:00.710 --> 28:05.579
...that we may never forget
how very fortunate we are. Amen.

28:05.748 --> 28:07.238
Amen.

28:09.252 --> 28:12.153
Let's check the score.
Up by 10.

28:13.589 --> 28:16.387
Collins, can you pass me
the green beans, please?

28:16.893 --> 28:21.125
Don't pick it with your fingers.
Just take- Take a sp- Ta-

28:23.766 --> 28:26.462
- SJ, elbows.
- Sorry.

28:29.705 --> 28:32.799
So, Big Mike. You like to shop?

28:34.744 --> 28:37.679
Because tomorrow I think I'm gonna
have to show you how it's done.

28:43.085 --> 28:44.950
I got clothes.

28:45.121 --> 28:47.180
You have clothes.

28:47.356 --> 28:50.848
And an extra T-shirt in a plastic bag
does not a wardrobe make.

28:51.260 --> 28:52.784
I have clothes.

28:52.962 --> 28:55.954
Fine, let's go get them.
Just tell me where I'm going.

29:06.208 --> 29:07.266
All right.

29:08.077 --> 29:13.606
Tell me everything I need to know about
you. Who takes care of you? A mother?

29:13.783 --> 29:17.913
Do you have a mother?
A grandmother maybe?

29:22.325 --> 29:26.455
Tell you what, Big Mike, we can do this
the easy way or we can do this the hard way.

29:26.629 --> 29:28.563
You take your pick.

29:31.600 --> 29:33.033
Fine.

29:33.336 --> 29:39.036
Tell me just one thing I should know
about you. Just- Just one.

29:41.277 --> 29:43.370
I don't like to be called Big Mike.

29:45.081 --> 29:46.480
Okay.

29:46.849 --> 29:50.717
Tell you what, from now on,
to me, you're Michael.

29:51.187 --> 29:52.745
Okay?

29:54.357 --> 29:56.518
So, Michael...

29:58.594 --> 30:00.186
...where are we headed?

30:00.363 --> 30:04.026
I kid y’all not, y’all. I'm gonna
tell it. Make it rain and everything, right?

30:04.200 --> 30:08.637
Shorty- Shorty gets to the top of the pole.
She just done-

30:12.174 --> 30:14.142
That's nice.
Yo, check it.

30:14.310 --> 30:17.302
What's that, a seven?
For real.

30:17.480 --> 30:19.243
Yeah.

30:19.915 --> 30:21.212
Yeah, right there.

30:21.384 --> 30:24.410
- You know them?
- Man, I ain't got no idea, shorty.

30:24.587 --> 30:26.953
This is where your mother lives?

30:27.356 --> 30:30.120
- Let's go get them.
- Don't- Don't get out.

30:30.292 --> 30:32.852
Who's gonna help you
carry your clothes, Michael?

30:36.132 --> 30:38.191
Don't get out the car.

30:44.673 --> 30:46.402
Snowflake.

30:47.009 --> 30:49.409
Oh. That's Big Mike, man.

30:50.046 --> 30:52.844
Oh, Big Mike is in the house.

30:54.450 --> 30:56.577
Big Mike! Where you been, baby?

30:59.488 --> 31:04.152
Hey, who that fine thing you got driving you
around now, like Miss Daisy or something?

31:04.326 --> 31:05.657
Hey, David.

31:05.828 --> 31:09.924
You need to holler at me about them
sneakers, man. I'm gonna take care of you.

31:13.102 --> 31:15.900
I run this over here in Hurt Village.
Baby, believe that.

31:19.742 --> 31:24.042
Ey. Hey, D, watch this. They always
go for the wink, watch this.

31:24.213 --> 31:27.307
There you go. Yeah, snowflake. Ha-ha-ha.

31:27.683 --> 31:30.413
You like that. Yeah.

32:06.021 --> 32:09.923
That girl will not listen to me.
She don't listen to nobody.

32:10.092 --> 32:12.959
- Hey, Mike.
- Hi, Big Mike.

32:20.736 --> 32:22.135
<i>She wasn't home.</i>

32:25.808 --> 32:29.209
Well, we can come back.

32:32.081 --> 32:35.107
She probably moved to a nicer place.

32:45.828 --> 32:50.060
I've been in Memphis my whole life
and never been anywhere near here.

32:51.700 --> 32:55.636
- You're gonna take care of me, right?
I got your back.

32:58.841 --> 33:01.366
Now just follow me, y’all. Uh-huh.

33:01.544 --> 33:03.102
There we go.

33:03.279 --> 33:06.305
Oh, we also got apparel for the ladies.

33:06.482 --> 33:09.940
But everything we got that'll fit him
is right here.

33:12.588 --> 33:13.680
This is it?

33:13.989 --> 33:17.288
If this is all you got, why's it say
"Big and Tall" on the sign?

33:17.459 --> 33:20.860
Big and Tall. You need
Bigger and Taller.

33:22.932 --> 33:25.059
- Holler if you need me.
Thank you.

33:25.234 --> 33:29.728
- See anything you like?
- Hey, I got just what you're looking for.

33:29.905 --> 33:31.896
One thing I know about shopping
is that...

33:32.074 --> 33:34.838
...if you don't love it in the store,
you won't wear it.

33:35.010 --> 33:36.978
The store's where you like it the best.

33:37.146 --> 33:40.445
So before you choose something,
think of yourself wearing it.

33:40.616 --> 33:43.744
Say to yourself, "Is this me?"

33:46.789 --> 33:48.586
What about this one?

33:52.962 --> 33:56.420
Well, this is not atrocious, this...

33:56.832 --> 34:00.632
No? All right, well, you go look
over there and I'll go look over here.

34:03.973 --> 34:07.636
Why would you need this many coats
out of plastic?

34:09.911 --> 34:14.143
Good Lord. What is this made out of?

34:18.420 --> 34:22.982
That's the one? That's the one you like?

34:24.927 --> 34:26.985
Well, all right, then.

34:40.943 --> 34:43.503
Have a great day! Learn something.

34:52.054 --> 34:54.112
Oh, don't get your panties in a wad.

34:56.859 --> 34:59.657
The best part about Paris was the food.

34:59.828 --> 35:02.228
They use sauce like we use gravy.

35:02.398 --> 35:05.663
- I had to join a gym the day I got back.
Oh.

35:07.236 --> 35:09.830
Have y’all spent much time
on the other side of town?

35:10.005 --> 35:13.304
- Where exactly are you talking about?
- Alabama Street, Hurt Village.

35:13.475 --> 35:15.807
Hurt Village? That sounds like a threat.

35:15.978 --> 35:17.411
Not far off.

35:17.579 --> 35:19.843
I think it might hurt me to go there.

35:20.015 --> 35:21.915
It would hurt your reputation
to go there.

35:22.084 --> 35:25.576
Actually, I'm from there but didn't mind
hard work, and look where I am now.

35:25.754 --> 35:27.415
Eating an $18 salad?

35:29.124 --> 35:30.887
And it's a little soggy, to be honest.

35:31.060 --> 35:34.655
What is this sudden interest in the projects?
Another one of your "charities"?

35:34.830 --> 35:38.960
Wait. Project for the projects.
Ooh. That's catchy!

35:39.134 --> 35:40.692
Y'all, money would raise itself.

35:40.869 --> 35:42.996
Okay. Count me in, Leigh Anne.

35:44.373 --> 35:47.069
- Break out your checkbooks.
Yes.

35:47.242 --> 35:50.803
SJ, you have two more minutes
on that Playbox thing, all right?

35:50.979 --> 35:53.004
Aw, Mom!
- There you go.

35:57.486 --> 35:59.954
Michael, do you wanna stay here?

36:02.658 --> 36:07.027
I mean, because if you wanna stay here
for a while longer...

36:07.196 --> 36:12.065
...I can find some time to
figure out a bedroom for you.

36:13.435 --> 36:15.130
I mean, because look at this.

36:15.304 --> 36:18.603
You have practically ruined
a $10,000 couch.

36:24.380 --> 36:26.439
Do you wanna stay here, Michael?

36:29.051 --> 36:31.542
I don't wanna go anyplace else.

36:36.925 --> 36:38.654
Well, all right, then.

36:41.563 --> 36:43.554
SJ, you better be off that Playbox.

36:43.732 --> 36:45.893
That wasn't two minutes.

36:46.535 --> 36:48.833
Good night, Mrs. Tuohy.

36:54.543 --> 36:57.979
I see on the admission that we're
Michael’s contact for medical emergencies.

36:58.147 --> 36:59.739
Sean wrote that in last week.

36:59.915 --> 37:03.009
We needed a contact number and
the ones listed weren't in service.

37:03.719 --> 37:05.914
I love that man.

37:06.989 --> 37:08.081
What's this?

37:09.258 --> 37:13.160
The state makes schools measure
for career aptitude in the eighth grade...

37:13.328 --> 37:16.388
- ...and this just came with his file.
- What's it say about Michael?

37:16.565 --> 37:19.329
Spatial relations, third percentile.

37:19.501 --> 37:22.766
Ability to learn, fifth percentile.

37:22.938 --> 37:27.432
It's funny though. He tested in
the 98th percentile in one category.

37:27.609 --> 37:30.476
- Which one?
- Protective instincts.

37:33.048 --> 37:37.451
So over here you have a desk,
chest of drawers...

37:37.619 --> 37:40.713
...you have a nightstand, a light,
an alarm.

37:40.889 --> 37:44.518
Sean says all pro athletes use futons
if they can’t find a bed big enough...

37:44.693 --> 37:47.560
...so I got you one of those.
Of course the frame was heinous.

37:47.729 --> 37:51.130
I was not about to let that in my house,
but I got you something nicer.

37:52.901 --> 37:56.064
- It's mine?
- Yes, sir.

37:57.139 --> 37:59.903
- What?
- Never had one before.

38:00.642 --> 38:02.405
What, a room to yourself?

38:03.145 --> 38:04.806
A bed.

38:14.189 --> 38:16.817
Well, you have one now.

38:48.524 --> 38:51.425
Okay. Define osmosis.

38:52.127 --> 38:54.391
I think I know that one.

38:55.097 --> 38:58.726
It's when water passes through
a barrier.

38:58.901 --> 39:01.392
That's basically right, Michael.
Very good.

39:09.177 --> 39:13.113
Name the combatants
in the Battle of Waterloo.

39:13.282 --> 39:16.012
I know that one. Um...

39:16.184 --> 39:17.947
- The little guy, Napoleon.
- Uh-huh.

39:18.120 --> 39:22.113
He was on one side
and a duke was on the other.

39:22.291 --> 39:23.781
Duke of Wellington.

39:23.959 --> 39:27.019
Yeah, and the Duke of Wellington,
he had Russians helping him.

39:27.195 --> 39:28.219
Prussians.

39:42.477 --> 39:47.210
Enough with the rugby shirts.
You look like a giant bumblebee.

39:49.551 --> 39:50.779
That Taco Bell.

39:50.953 --> 39:54.719
KFC catty-corner. And
the Long John Silver’s on the next block.

39:54.890 --> 39:55.914
You own all of them?

39:56.091 --> 39:58.821
- Yeah. We've got like hundreds.
- Eighty-five.

39:59.094 --> 40:01.289
Is that why Mr. Tuohy
don't have to go to work?

40:01.530 --> 40:05.489
Whoa, whoa! Hey! I'm working even
when I'm not working.

40:06.234 --> 40:09.328
- What?
- And you eat at all these places for free?

40:09.504 --> 40:11.472
All you want. It's awesome.

40:11.640 --> 40:14.575
What do y’all do with all
the leftover food from the restaurant?

40:14.743 --> 40:17.109
We have to throw some out,
what's already cooked.

40:17.279 --> 40:20.077
- That's too bad.
- Yeah, I'd rather sell it.

40:20.248 --> 40:22.580
Seems like you could give it away
or something.

40:22.751 --> 40:26.551
- You should check into that, Daddy.
All right, I will, SJ.

40:26.722 --> 40:29.520
How come we're not eating
at one of your restaurants tonight?

40:29.691 --> 40:33.149
- Well, because tonight is a special occasion.
What?

40:33.695 --> 40:37.153
I talked to Coach Cotton. He said
Michael’s grades have improved enough...

40:37.332 --> 40:40.165
...that he can go out
for spring football in March.

40:40.335 --> 40:43.702
- Isn't that great?
- Oh, man! You're gonna crush some people!

40:51.046 --> 40:53.844
- Hey, guys, how we doing?
- Great, thank you.

40:54.716 --> 40:58.174
I've got a design book I need to get.
Why don't you check our reservation?

40:58.353 --> 41:00.253
They'll seat us right away.
Can't it wait?

41:00.422 --> 41:02.890
They might be closed by then.
Come on, SJ!

41:03.058 --> 41:04.582
I need some new magazines.

41:06.962 --> 41:08.862
Michael, come on. Come on.

41:20.008 --> 41:23.341
Collins? Collins?

41:23.812 --> 41:26.337
Collins, come on, your dad's
already PO'd. Let's go.

41:26.515 --> 41:27.709
Over here.

41:36.091 --> 41:40.790
You remember this one, Mom?
You read it to us like a thousand times.

41:41.196 --> 41:44.893
"He gnashed his terrible teeth
and he roared his terrible roar."

41:45.967 --> 41:47.867
I always liked this one.

41:48.036 --> 41:49.401
<i>Mm. Ferdinand.</i>

41:49.705 --> 41:51.536
Me too.

41:51.740 --> 41:55.232
Michael, your mama ever read
either one of those books to you?

41:58.480 --> 42:00.038
No?

42:00.749 --> 42:02.307
How cute!

42:02.484 --> 42:03.974
It was a good steak, huh?

42:04.152 --> 42:05.141
Thank you, Daddy.

42:05.320 --> 42:06.878
Thank you for a lovely dinner, Papa.

42:07.055 --> 42:08.420
Here we go.

42:43.625 --> 42:48.358
Michael. Who was that boy
you were talking to at the restaurant?

42:48.530 --> 42:50.498
Marcus.

42:51.166 --> 42:55.262
- Marcus, and he- He works there?
- Yeah.

42:56.371 --> 42:58.202
How do you know him?

42:59.741 --> 43:01.936
He's my brother.

43:08.483 --> 43:11.384
Well, we'd really- We'd really
like to meet him someday.

43:12.621 --> 43:14.919
Would that be okay with you?

43:15.390 --> 43:17.324
I don't know where he stays.

43:18.026 --> 43:20.517
When was the last time you saw him?

43:23.365 --> 43:24.923
When I was little, maybe.

43:29.571 --> 43:33.632
<i>"Once upon a time in Spain,
there was a little bull...</i>

43:33.809 --> 43:36.972
...and his name was Ferdinand.

43:37.345 --> 43:40.644
All the other little bulls he lived with
would run and jump...

43:40.816 --> 43:43.546
...and butt their heads together.

43:44.186 --> 43:46.711
But not Ferdinand.

43:47.889 --> 43:53.691
He liked to sit just quietly
and smell the flowers.

43:54.796 --> 43:58.596
He had a favorite spot out
in the pasture under a cork tree.

44:00.202 --> 44:02.329
<i>It was his favorite tree...</i>

44:02.504 --> 44:08.067
<i>...and he would sit in its shade
all day and smell the flowers. "</i>

44:08.243 --> 44:11.007
- Good night.
- Good night.

44:13.381 --> 44:15.975
- What?
- What?

44:16.251 --> 44:18.378
Why are you smiling?

44:18.653 --> 44:23.022
I don't know, I'm just happy.
Real happy.

44:23.191 --> 44:26.160
Does this happiness have anything
to do with Michael?

44:26.328 --> 44:27.955
No.

44:28.763 --> 44:31.664
It has everything to do with Michael.

44:33.034 --> 44:35.525
Mm. Mm.

44:35.770 --> 44:37.738
- Happy's good.
- Mm.

44:38.240 --> 44:40.367
You know what I think we should do?

44:40.542 --> 44:43.340
We should start a charity
for kids like Michael.

44:43.511 --> 44:45.945
- Okay.
- Maybe fund a program at Wingate.

44:46.114 --> 44:47.138
Sure.

44:47.315 --> 44:49.579
Lord knows that school
could use a little color.

44:49.751 --> 44:53.346
Poor Michael’s like a fly in the milk
in that place.

44:53.521 --> 44:55.421
Are you listening to me?

44:57.259 --> 45:01.889
- Hmm?
- I try to concentrate on one...

45:02.697 --> 45:04.358
...thing...

45:04.799 --> 45:06.460
...at a time.

45:06.635 --> 45:08.330
You knew I was a multitasker...

45:08.503 --> 45:09.868
...when you married me, right?

45:10.038 --> 45:14.099
- I sure did.
- Right. Okay, just checking.

45:17.913 --> 45:22.282
Okay, Tuohy family.
Big smiles, everyone.

45:23.084 --> 45:26.986
And one, two, three!

45:29.424 --> 45:30.448
Michael.

45:30.625 --> 45:32.752
Come on down here
and get in the next one.

45:32.961 --> 45:35.953
Come on. Come on. Come on down.

45:41.303 --> 45:44.363
Oh, come on. It's not like I'm gonna
put it on the Christmas card.

45:44.539 --> 45:48.839
Okay, let's scootch in a little tighter.

45:49.010 --> 45:50.534
That's good.

45:51.313 --> 45:52.644
Really big smiles.

45:52.814 --> 45:55.476
Okay, one, two, three.

45:55.650 --> 45:57.447
- Say "Rebels!"
Rebels!

46:01.656 --> 46:04.181
<i>- a blitz off
the corner, quick pass over the middle.</i>

46:04.359 --> 46:08.625
<i>- The hot route was there. And that's...
I got it.</i>

46:09.297 --> 46:11.629
- Who's winning?
- Tennessee.

46:11.800 --> 46:14.462
- Ugh. Who they playing?
- Clemson.

46:14.636 --> 46:17.298
Your mama roots against Tennessee
no matter who they play?

46:17.472 --> 46:19.906
Uh- Yes, I do. With gusto.

46:20.075 --> 46:21.975
She can’t stand Tennessee.

46:22.143 --> 46:25.203
Collie-bell, I thought you were
going over to your boyfriend's.

46:25.380 --> 46:27.245
Thought I'd hang around here
for the day.

46:28.116 --> 46:29.549
Hmm.

46:29.784 --> 46:31.342
I like that.

46:31.519 --> 46:34.420
There's a couple messages on the machine.
I didn't check them.

46:34.589 --> 46:36.022
All right.

46:36.992 --> 46:40.393
<i>Hey, Sean, hey, Leigh Anne, it's
your cousin Bobby. Happy New Year's.</i>

46:40.628 --> 46:43.495
- Listen, I've had about five cold ones...
- Of course you have.

46:43.665 --> 46:45.724
<i>...so I'm just gonna go ahead and ask:</i>

46:46.301 --> 46:49.634
Did y’all know there's a colored boy
in your Christmas card?

46:52.674 --> 46:54.403
What?

46:55.010 --> 46:58.002
You just looked teeny-tiny next to him.

46:58.179 --> 47:00.147
Right? Like Jessica Lange and King Kong.

47:01.549 --> 47:04.143
Hey, does Michael get
the family discount at Taco Bell?

47:04.319 --> 47:07.846
Because if he does,
Sean's gonna lose a few stores.

47:08.023 --> 47:09.081
He's a good kid.

47:09.257 --> 47:12.192
Well, I say you make it official
and just adopt him.

47:13.962 --> 47:18.262
He's gonna be 18 in a few months. Doesn't
really make much sense to legally adopt.

47:21.436 --> 47:22.460
Leigh Anne.

47:22.937 --> 47:25.462
Is this some sort of white-guilt thing?

47:25.807 --> 47:28.105
What will your daddy say?

47:28.810 --> 47:32.109
Um... Before or after
he turns over in his grave?

47:32.280 --> 47:34.748
Daddy's been gone five years, Elaine.

47:34.916 --> 47:38.044
Make matters worse, you were
at the funeral. Remember?

47:38.219 --> 47:40.585
You wore Chanel
and that awful black hat.

47:40.755 --> 47:42.552
Look, here's the deal.

47:42.724 --> 47:45.955
I don't need y’all to approve
my choices, all right?

47:46.127 --> 47:50.291
But I do ask that you respect them. You
have no idea what this boy's been through.

47:50.465 --> 47:53.127
And if this is gonna become
some running diatribe...

47:53.301 --> 47:55.997
...I can find an overpriced salad
a lot closer to home.

47:58.006 --> 48:01.373
- Leigh Anne, I'm sorry. We didn't intend to-
- No, we didn't, really.

48:01.543 --> 48:04.774
I think what you're doing is so great.

48:04.946 --> 48:07.710
To open up your home to him?

48:08.083 --> 48:10.347
Honey, you're changing that boy's life.

48:11.186 --> 48:12.778
No.

48:13.321 --> 48:14.913
He's changing mine.

48:16.491 --> 48:18.823
And that’s awesome for you,
but what about Collins?

48:20.662 --> 48:22.960
- What about Collins?
Aren't you worried?

48:23.131 --> 48:24.826
I mean, even just a little?

48:24.999 --> 48:29.436
He's a boy, a large, black boy,
sleeping under the same roof.

48:32.140 --> 48:33.437
Shame on you.

48:38.646 --> 48:39.977
I've got this.

48:42.083 --> 48:43.880
<i>Be honest with me, okay?</i>

48:45.787 --> 48:49.450
Does Michael being here
make you uncomfortable?

48:50.091 --> 48:53.527
They're stupid kids.
Who cares what they say?

48:53.695 --> 48:56.858
- What kids?
- At school.

48:57.365 --> 48:58.696
They're juvenile.

48:58.867 --> 49:00.892
And what do the juvenile kids say?

49:01.970 --> 49:04.200
It's really not worth repeating.

49:05.340 --> 49:07.240
And don't worry about SJ.

49:07.542 --> 49:11.740
He likes all the attention. He introduces
Michael as his big brother.

49:16.451 --> 49:17.816
And what about you?

49:18.219 --> 49:20.187
It's fine.

49:21.990 --> 49:25.084
I mean, you can’t just throw him
out on the street.

49:25.260 --> 49:27.421
I could make other arrangements.

49:31.432 --> 49:33.992
Hi, Mike.
- Hi. Need a push?

49:34.169 --> 49:35.796
Yes.

49:40.875 --> 49:43.400
Oh.
Higher, Mike, higher!

49:47.215 --> 49:49.206
Higher!

49:53.421 --> 49:55.582
Higher!

49:59.260 --> 50:02.388
Don't look down, don't look down. Ah!

50:35.630 --> 50:38.599
- Where are you going?
- Collins?

50:50.211 --> 50:52.509
Quit looking at me like that.

50:52.680 --> 50:55.615
I mean, we study together at home.

51:12.333 --> 51:16.793
You know how much those things weigh?
This kid's gonna make us all famous.

51:18.506 --> 51:22.738
Easy, Bert, man. It's only the spring.
He hasn't even had his first practice yet.

51:22.910 --> 51:24.935
No, he's a player.

51:25.380 --> 51:26.870
Break!

51:27.348 --> 51:29.316
Ready.
Break!

51:29.917 --> 51:33.580
Get down, son.
Get down in your stance. In your stance!

51:33.855 --> 51:34.879
Go!

51:36.090 --> 51:39.856
Shuck him, shuck him! Ah, ah-

51:40.928 --> 51:44.022
Mike, son, you-
You fought off the block...

51:44.198 --> 51:46.530
...but then you wanna shuck
the blocker.

51:46.701 --> 51:49.670
All right? Shuck him. All right, let's go.

51:50.471 --> 51:52.200
Huddle up.

51:52.373 --> 51:54.102
Papa.

51:55.476 --> 51:56.875
How's he doing?

51:57.045 --> 51:58.569
Hasn't quite gotten the hang of it yet.

52:06.721 --> 52:07.813
Mike, son.

52:07.989 --> 52:10.082
Shuck the blocker, don't tote him!

52:10.258 --> 52:12.192
Set, go!

52:13.594 --> 52:17.223
No, no, no! No, no, no!

52:17.965 --> 52:19.523
Set, go!

52:28.242 --> 52:30.039
Balloons! They're balloons!

52:30.678 --> 52:33.613
Guys, quit looking at the balloons.
Everybody!

52:33.781 --> 52:36.648
Most kids from bad situations
can’t wait to be violent...

52:36.818 --> 52:38.445
...and that comes out on the field.

52:38.619 --> 52:41.782
But this kid, he acts like
he doesn't wanna hit anyone.

52:41.956 --> 52:43.856
He's Ferdinand the Bull.

52:44.025 --> 52:45.754
What?
- Nothing.

52:47.261 --> 52:51.823
I thought he was gonna be a player. I can’t
believe I used up all my chips to get him in.

52:51.999 --> 52:54.160
I thought you said
it was your Christian duty.

52:55.870 --> 52:58.566
Look, Bert, he's never even played before.

52:59.640 --> 53:02.939
Yeah, and he won't this fall if he
doesn't improve a lot before then.

53:03.277 --> 53:05.142
Who died and made him Bear Bryant?

53:06.848 --> 53:08.213
Unbelievable.

53:09.350 --> 53:11.477
Oh, God bless me.

53:11.652 --> 53:13.313
This is your summer workout sheet.

53:13.488 --> 53:15.718
Now, first it says to warm up
and get loose.

53:16.657 --> 53:18.420
Well, go ahead, get loose.

53:21.295 --> 53:22.853
Are you loose?

53:23.231 --> 53:26.997
Okay. Next, it's five 100-yard runs
to stretch out your legs.

53:27.168 --> 53:29.432
- Can we just go home and play video games?
- Look!

53:29.604 --> 53:32.767
Everybody at Wingate is expecting you
to be a star football player.

53:32.940 --> 53:34.567
Don't wanna let them down,
do you?

53:34.742 --> 53:36.676
- I don't know.
- What about Dad and Mom?

53:36.844 --> 53:39.506
Because, you see, in our family,
everyone's an athlete.

53:39.680 --> 53:43.741
Dad was a basketball star.
Collins plays volleyball and runs track.

53:43.918 --> 53:46.250
And me, well, as you know, I do it all.

53:46.421 --> 53:48.912
And Mom- Well, Mom was a cheerleader...

53:49.090 --> 53:52.821
...which doesn't exactly count,
but don't tell her I said that. Okay?

53:52.994 --> 53:55.155
- Okay.
- Okay.

53:56.764 --> 53:59.824
- Yeah. Fifty.
Uhn.

54:00.001 --> 54:01.935
Fifty-one.

54:02.270 --> 54:05.603
Fifty-two. Fifty-three.

54:05.807 --> 54:08.970
Come on, you can get him.
Go, go, go! Come on!

54:09.143 --> 54:10.633
Five seconds left in the game!

54:12.513 --> 54:13.980
This way!

54:14.148 --> 54:15.308
This way!

54:15.483 --> 54:19.920
High knees, high knees, high knees!
Speed kills, baby! Run like the wind!

54:21.289 --> 54:22.916
Go, Michael, go!

54:23.124 --> 54:24.955
Ninety-eight.

54:25.359 --> 54:26.383
Ninety-nine.

54:28.229 --> 54:29.526
One hundred.

54:29.697 --> 54:32.393
Move your feet, move your feet!
Come on, come on! Go!

54:32.567 --> 54:33.898
- There you go.
- Ahh!

54:34.068 --> 54:36.468
You gotta get the tackle,
come on, come on, come on!

54:37.205 --> 54:38.467
Come on, Michael.

55:03.097 --> 55:04.121
Mrs. Tuohy?

55:04.298 --> 55:07.734
I hear "Mrs. Tuohy," I look over
my shoulder for my mother-in-law.

55:07.902 --> 55:11.030
Call me Leigh Anne or Mama
or almost anything else.

55:14.175 --> 55:17.167
- Can you help me get something?
- What?

55:19.614 --> 55:20.842
Driver's license.

55:22.750 --> 55:26.083
Why do you need a driver's license
when you don't even have a car?

55:33.528 --> 55:36.053
Michael, why do you want
a driver's license?

55:36.764 --> 55:39.631
It's something to carry
with my name on it.

55:46.874 --> 55:49.399
There's no one by the name of
Michael Oher in the system.

55:49.577 --> 55:51.977
Another last name, perhaps?

55:54.215 --> 55:56.911
Look, I will sign something
that says he lives with us.

55:57.084 --> 56:00.144
We'll pay for all of the insurance.
Whatever it takes. Okay?

56:01.122 --> 56:02.316
What's it gonna take?

56:02.490 --> 56:05.220
You wanna do what?
- You heard me.

56:05.393 --> 56:08.658
- Shouldn’t we at least talk about this?
- What do you think we're doing?

56:08.829 --> 56:10.922
And don't act like
I'm going behind your back.

56:11.098 --> 56:14.625
I know you put us down as
Michael’s medical contact at school.

56:14.802 --> 56:17.737
There is a huge difference
between paying for a broken arm...

56:17.905 --> 56:21.602
...and being legally responsible for
someone. I mean, a kid we barely know.

56:21.776 --> 56:25.075
That's another thing. We need to
find out more about his past.

56:25.246 --> 56:29.307
He won't talk about it. He's like an onion.
You have to peel him back a layer at a time.

56:29.483 --> 56:31.747
Not if you use a knife.

56:32.453 --> 56:35.616
What if we took him to a child
psychologist or something?

56:35.790 --> 56:38.452
- Do you really expect Big Mike to-?
- Michael.

56:38.626 --> 56:40.560
Do you expect Michael
to lie on a couch...

56:40.728 --> 56:43.253
...and talk about his childhood
like he's Woody Allen?

56:43.431 --> 56:46.093
I mean, Michael’s gift
is his ability to forget.

56:46.267 --> 56:50.226
He's mad at no one and he really
doesn't care what happened in the past.

56:50.871 --> 56:51.997
You're right.

56:52.707 --> 56:55.972
Excuse me? "You're right"?

56:56.143 --> 56:58.611
How'd those words taste
coming out of your mouth?

56:58.779 --> 57:00.212
Like vinegar.

57:09.056 --> 57:11.786
Well, at least promise me
you'll think about it.

57:11.959 --> 57:13.756
All right.

57:14.462 --> 57:17.829
"All right, you’ll think about it,"
or, "All right, we should do it"?

57:17.999 --> 57:20.229
Is there a difference?

57:22.436 --> 57:27.703
Just tell Gerald to hold on to the chiffonier
and I will be by there after a while.

57:28.142 --> 57:31.976
You know- I gotta call you back. Bye.

57:33.681 --> 57:35.672
Excuse me.

57:36.884 --> 57:38.476
I'm not cutting, I'm just asking.

57:38.653 --> 57:42.316
Let me tell you something. We have been
sitting around here for over an hour...

57:42.490 --> 57:46.722
...and when I look around and all I see are
people shooting the bull and drinking coffee.

57:46.894 --> 57:48.088
Who runs this place?

57:51.365 --> 57:53.925
I'd have it in shape in two days,
I can tell you that.

57:54.101 --> 57:57.161
- I bet you would. How can I help you?
- Oh, he was first.

57:57.338 --> 58:00.637
- No, you go ahead. I think I wanna hear this.
- Me too.

58:00.808 --> 58:02.537
I do not appreciate the attitude.

58:02.710 --> 58:05.508
Ma'am, now, you can tell me
what you want...

58:05.680 --> 58:07.875
...or I can make sure
you wait here all day.

58:08.049 --> 58:09.539
Now, how can I help you?

58:09.917 --> 58:11.817
I would like to become a legal guardian.

58:12.086 --> 58:14.281
Lord help that child.

58:17.858 --> 58:22.192
There's very little on Michael.
Most of his files have been lost.

58:22.363 --> 58:25.355
- Well, what is in there?
- A few case notes.

58:25.900 --> 58:30.360
This one describes an incident where
officers forcibly removed Michael...

58:30.538 --> 58:33.268
...from Denise Oher's care
when Michael was 7.

58:33.441 --> 58:36.239
Quite a scene evidently.
They had to split up the kids.

58:36.410 --> 58:39.937
- And it's far from the worst.
- Where is she? His mother?

58:40.114 --> 58:44.414
I don't know. If you find her, we got
a heap more files we could add to.

58:45.453 --> 58:47.045
Well, how many kids does she have?

58:47.221 --> 58:50.384
Least a dozen, probably. If not more.

58:50.558 --> 58:54.221
With her drug-arrest record, my guess
would be, she can’t even remember.

58:54.395 --> 58:56.090
Can I see that?

59:00.568 --> 59:03.128
So we would need her permission,
right?

59:03.304 --> 59:07.968
No. Michael is a ward of the state.
Just apply and get a judge to sign off on it.

59:10.745 --> 59:14.841
So you would just give him away
without even telling his mother?

59:29.029 --> 59:31.293
Check out this piece right here.

59:31.465 --> 59:33.126
Yeah.
Damn, girl.

59:38.472 --> 59:39.461
<i>Miss Oher?</i>

59:43.277 --> 59:46.303
Hi. Miss- Miss Oher?

59:48.048 --> 59:51.279
- You from the state?
- No.

59:51.485 --> 59:54.511
My name is Leigh Anne Tuohy,
and your son...

59:54.855 --> 59:57.824
...Michael, lives with me...

59:58.492 --> 01:00:00.585
...and my family.

01:00:06.967 --> 01:00:09.993
How is my boy? How's Big Mike?

01:00:10.171 --> 01:00:13.265
He's fine. He's doing real well.

01:00:14.008 --> 01:00:16.499
We might have some wine in the kitchen,
if you...

01:00:16.677 --> 01:00:18.668
Oh, no, no. That's real kind.

01:00:19.046 --> 01:00:20.877
When did you last see Michael?

01:00:22.449 --> 01:00:24.417
I don't know.

01:00:24.585 --> 01:00:28.749
How many-? How many foster kids
you got living with you?

01:00:28.923 --> 01:00:33.019
Oh, I'm not a foster parent to Michael.
We're just helping him out.

01:00:33.360 --> 01:00:34.918
State don't pay you nothing?

01:00:35.229 --> 01:00:37.163
No, no.

01:00:37.331 --> 01:00:40.767
And you feed him and
you buy him clothes too?

01:00:40.935 --> 01:00:43.904
Well, when we can find them
in his size.

01:00:47.107 --> 01:00:49.405
You are a fine Christian lady.

01:00:49.777 --> 01:00:52.109
Well, I try to be.

01:00:53.414 --> 01:00:55.814
This all real nice, what you're doing...

01:00:55.983 --> 01:00:59.441
...but don't be surprised if one day
you wake up and he gone.

01:01:00.621 --> 01:01:01.883
What do you mean?

01:01:02.056 --> 01:01:06.686
He's a runner. That's what the state
called him after they took him from me.

01:01:09.597 --> 01:01:12.259
Every foster home they sent him to...

01:01:12.600 --> 01:01:15.831
...he'd slip out the window at night
and come looking for me.

01:01:16.003 --> 01:01:21.270
No matter where I was, that boy
would come find me, take care of me.

01:01:23.143 --> 01:01:26.806
I've had some health problems.

01:01:27.948 --> 01:01:32.044
Miss Oher, was Michael born
under a different name?

01:01:32.887 --> 01:01:36.880
Proctor. That was his daddy's last name.

01:01:37.391 --> 01:01:38.722
Where is he?

01:01:38.893 --> 01:01:42.727
- I ain't seen him since he left.
- And when was that?

01:01:42.897 --> 01:01:44.956
Week after Mike was born.

01:01:45.933 --> 01:01:47.992
Do you happen to have
his birth certificate?

01:01:56.225 --> 01:01:59.558
It's all right. I'll figure it out.

01:02:13.842 --> 01:02:16.868
Mrs. Oher, you’ll always be
Michael’s mama.

01:02:20.883 --> 01:02:22.316
Would you like to see him?

01:02:22.484 --> 01:02:26.386
No. Not this way.

01:02:28.657 --> 01:02:30.921
It's Williams.

01:02:32.427 --> 01:02:35.089
His last name's Williams.

01:02:36.665 --> 01:02:39.964
Couldn’t even remember
who the boy's father is.

01:03:08.297 --> 01:03:12.358
I checked out the new Madden. The colors
are better, graphics brighter. It's awesome.

01:03:12.534 --> 01:03:15.128
Michael, we have something
we'd like to ask you.

01:03:15.804 --> 01:03:20.241
- What?
- Well, Leigh Anne and I, we-

01:03:20.509 --> 01:03:24.707
Well, we'd like to become
your legal guardians.

01:03:25.080 --> 01:03:26.138
What's that mean?

01:03:26.582 --> 01:03:29.574
What it means is,
is that we wanna know...

01:03:29.751 --> 01:03:33.050
...if you would like to
become part of this family.

01:03:41.863 --> 01:03:43.728
Kind of thought I already was.

01:03:52.574 --> 01:03:55.168
Well, all right, then.

01:04:02.851 --> 01:04:04.614
Right here.

01:04:08.690 --> 01:04:11.386
You got a couple steps.
Better watch that big foot.

01:04:11.560 --> 01:04:12.788
One more.

01:04:12.961 --> 01:04:15.259
One more. There you go.

01:04:16.331 --> 01:04:18.731
All right. Take off the blindfold.

01:04:22.904 --> 01:04:27.398
Well? That's the one you wanted,
isn't it? Heh.

01:04:27.576 --> 01:04:31.012
Here. Here you go, go ahead.
Take it for a ride. Go on.

01:04:31.179 --> 01:04:34.148
Can I go too?
- Yeah, but, Michael? Be careful.

01:04:34.316 --> 01:04:36.307
Shotgun!

01:04:36.485 --> 01:04:37.952
Whoo-hoo!

01:04:39.087 --> 01:04:42.682
- He wanted a truck?
- Well, Michael thinks he's a redneck.

01:04:42.858 --> 01:04:44.792
Come on, Michael!

01:04:45.394 --> 01:04:49.194
Okay. See, you're the ketchup,
here at left tackle on the weak side.

01:04:49.364 --> 01:04:52.299
The first play is simple. Gap.

01:04:54.336 --> 01:04:58.329
Now, see, this just means that you're
going to block whoever's in front of you...

01:04:58.507 --> 01:05:01.704
...or on your inside shoulder, if
you're not covered by a defender.

01:05:01.877 --> 01:05:05.369
Now, I'll be the running back, and you
show me what you're supposed to do.

01:05:05.714 --> 01:05:07.113
Ready? Hike!

01:05:07.616 --> 01:05:11.484
You'll block him. He'll hit him.
Quarterback'll hand it off.

01:05:11.653 --> 01:05:13.518
He gets the ball, and he takes off!

01:05:13.689 --> 01:05:16.283
Open lane to the end zone.
All there is to it.

01:05:16.458 --> 01:05:17.720
What's going on here?

01:05:18.560 --> 01:05:20.221
Blended spice just scored.

01:05:20.395 --> 01:05:23.387
We were going through the playbook.
Michael got moved to offense.

01:05:23.565 --> 01:05:26.898
When you're done, put the players
back in the spice cabinet. Thank you.

01:05:27.069 --> 01:05:28.536
No problem.

01:05:28.870 --> 01:05:32.601
Actually, Mom, we were
kind of waiting for you.

01:05:32.774 --> 01:05:34.708
You see,
the new Madden game came out...

01:05:34.876 --> 01:05:37.174
...and me and Michael
were wanting to go get it.

01:05:37.345 --> 01:05:40.974
- I can’t, I've got a meeting in 10 minutes.
- But he can drive.

01:05:41.216 --> 01:05:42.979
He can drive us.

01:05:45.787 --> 01:05:47.482
Oh, yeah, that’s what I'm talking about.

01:05:47.656 --> 01:05:50.124
What you know about this?
I know a lot about this.

01:05:50.292 --> 01:05:52.385
- Show me something then.
- I'll show you something.

01:05:52.561 --> 01:05:54.620
- I'll start it. Follow my lead.
- All right.

01:05:54.796 --> 01:05:55.922
- You ready?
- Yeah.

01:05:56.098 --> 01:05:57.156
<i>Next day's function</i>

01:05:57.332 --> 01:05:58.697
<i>High-class luncheon</i>

01:05:58.867 --> 01:06:00.357
<i>- Food is served
- And you're stone-cold munchin'</i>

01:06:00.535 --> 01:06:02.366
<i>- Music comes on
- People start to dance</i>

01:06:02.537 --> 01:06:04.528
<i>- But then you ate so much
- You nearly split your pants</i>

01:06:04.706 --> 01:06:06.537
<i>- A girl starts walkin'
- Guy starts gawkin'</i>

01:06:06.708 --> 01:06:08.300
<i>- Sits down next to you
- Starts talkin'</i>

01:06:08.477 --> 01:06:10.741
<i>- Says she wanna dance
- 'Cause she likes the groove</i>

01:06:10.912 --> 01:06:13.107
<i>- So come on, fatso
- And just bust a move</i>

01:06:13.281 --> 01:06:17.217
<i>If you want it
You got it</i>

01:06:17.385 --> 01:06:21.185
<i>You want it
Baby, you got it</i>

01:06:21.356 --> 01:06:25.349
<i>You want it
You got it</i>

01:06:25.527 --> 01:06:29.054
<i>You want it
Baby, you got it</i>

01:06:33.034 --> 01:06:34.899
This is not a $40,000 Oushak, Omid.

01:06:36.271 --> 01:06:37.363
You're crazy, Leigh Anne.

01:06:37.539 --> 01:06:40.770
The borders are different widths.
They've been altered.

01:06:40.942 --> 01:06:44.776
We'll give you 17, tops, all right? Hello.

01:06:48.850 --> 01:06:50.681
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Ma'am, you can’t get through.

01:06:50.852 --> 01:06:53.252
Those are my kids. Those are my kids.

01:06:55.724 --> 01:06:57.988
- Oh, my God.
Please, God, let him be okay.

01:06:58.160 --> 01:07:00.185
Where are they?!
I'm so sorry!

01:07:00.362 --> 01:07:04.458
- Michael, are you okay?
- I'm fine! SJ! Go help SJ!

01:07:05.133 --> 01:07:07.658
I'm so sorry. So sorry.

01:07:08.136 --> 01:07:09.797
How are his vitals?

01:07:09.971 --> 01:07:11.529
Excuse me, ma'am.
- That's my son.

01:07:11.706 --> 01:07:13.970
SJ. SJ, baby.

01:07:14.142 --> 01:07:15.769
- Mama?
- Yes, baby?

01:07:15.944 --> 01:07:18.310
Do you think the blood'll
come out of my shirt?

01:07:19.815 --> 01:07:23.148
Yes, I think the blood
will come out of your shirt.

01:07:23.318 --> 01:07:25.081
An air bag deploys at 200 miles an hour.

01:07:25.253 --> 01:07:27.380
Your son is too small
to be in the front seat.

01:07:27.556 --> 01:07:29.148
But he is okay, right?

01:07:29.324 --> 01:07:33.124
Busted lip, bruised face. Usually when
someone his size gets hit with a air bag...

01:07:33.295 --> 01:07:35.820
...it's a fractured face, broken neck,
maybe worse.

01:07:35.997 --> 01:07:39.797
It's like the air bag was coming for him
and changed direction.

01:07:39.968 --> 01:07:42.129
It's probably defective or something...

01:07:42.304 --> 01:07:44.636
...but your son's very, very lucky.

01:07:44.806 --> 01:07:48.173
No, I did. I called the insurance,
it's fine. It's fine.

01:07:48.343 --> 01:07:50.277
I'll talk to you later. I gotta go. Bye.

