Pros? Are we even sure
he's gonna get college offers?

01:27:10.771 --> 01:27:13.262
<i>Michael, Nick Saban from LSU.</i>

01:27:13.440 --> 01:27:15.806
<i>Looking forward to you
coming down and visiting.</i>

01:27:15.976 --> 01:27:18.945
<i>Greetings, I'm Lou Holtz
from South Carolina. I'm call-</i>

01:27:19.113 --> 01:27:22.605
<i>We are very interested in having
Michael over to Knoxville for a visit.</i>

01:27:23.851 --> 01:27:25.079
Phil Fulmer, Tennessee.

01:27:25.252 --> 01:27:29.655
There's 20 more of them on there.
And these things right here, 50 of them.

01:27:29.823 --> 01:27:31.290
- Any of those from Ole Miss?
- No.

01:27:31.458 --> 01:27:34.393
They're not gonna start recruiting
till they hire another coach.

01:27:34.561 --> 01:27:38.292
Doesn't make any difference
unless Michael makes his grades. Ahem.

01:27:39.666 --> 01:27:40.690
What are we gonna do?

01:27:42.844 --> 01:27:45.938
I understand you applied
for a teaching position at Wingate.

01:27:47.181 --> 01:27:48.978
I wasn't religious enough for them.

01:27:49.617 --> 01:27:55.180
I'm a spiritual person, Mrs. Tuohy,
but I have certain, shall we say, doubts.

01:27:56.257 --> 01:27:58.282
Well, I appreciate your honesty,
Miss Sue.

01:27:58.659 --> 01:28:00.251
What's the situation with Michael?

01:28:00.428 --> 01:28:02.896
- He needs to do better in school.
- Obviously.

01:28:03.064 --> 01:28:04.326
But why the big push?

01:28:04.498 --> 01:28:08.559
Well, he's in line for a football
scholarship if he gets his grades up.

01:28:08.736 --> 01:28:11.899
- Is he considering Ole Miss?
- Better be.

01:28:13.307 --> 01:28:14.865
I'd love to work with him.

01:28:15.042 --> 01:28:17.442
Well, when would you like to start?

01:28:18.312 --> 01:28:22.180
Mrs. Tuohy, um, there's something
you should know about me.

01:28:22.350 --> 01:28:24.045
I don't usually tell many people...

01:28:24.218 --> 01:28:27.881
...but it's something I feel you should
be aware of before you hire me.

01:28:28.556 --> 01:28:30.615
Uh- What is it?

01:28:31.525 --> 01:28:33.049
I'm a Democrat.

01:28:35.196 --> 01:28:36.959
Okay.

01:28:42.236 --> 01:28:44.761
- I don't understand it.
- Yet.

01:28:44.939 --> 01:28:47.203
You don't understand it yet.

01:28:49.010 --> 01:28:50.500
How big is your head, Michael?

01:28:50.745 --> 01:28:52.076
Big.

01:28:52.246 --> 01:28:53.679
And what's in there?

01:28:53.848 --> 01:28:55.145
- A brain.
- A brain.

01:28:55.316 --> 01:28:57.011
It's full of knowledge.

01:28:57.184 --> 01:29:01.814
Like a file cabinet with maps,
and shortcuts for figuring things out.

01:29:02.490 --> 01:29:06.324
You'll get there, Michael Oher, because
I'm here to help you use those maps...

01:29:06.494 --> 01:29:10.521
...and reach your destination,
like Sacagawea led Lewis and Clark.

01:29:10.698 --> 01:29:11.926
Sacagawea?

01:29:12.099 --> 01:29:15.466
We'll get to that.
And the history books have it wrong.

01:29:15.636 --> 01:29:18.833
All you need to know
is I'll get you there.

01:29:19.640 --> 01:29:21.631
Do you believe me?

01:29:24.412 --> 01:29:26.039
You trust me, Michael?

01:29:28.282 --> 01:29:29.306
Yes, Miss Sue.

01:29:32.153 --> 01:29:33.347
Try it again.

01:29:34.889 --> 01:29:37.722
What's the next one? Read that
to me. Okay, what does it say?

01:29:37.892 --> 01:29:42.329
First we have to find the constant.
Now, where is the constant?

01:29:42.930 --> 01:29:45.091
Good. See?

01:29:45.266 --> 01:29:48.463
Who'd have thought we'd have
a black son before we knew a Democrat?

01:29:50.638 --> 01:29:53.835
Doorbell!
I got it, guys.

01:29:56.444 --> 01:29:58.503
Coach, how are you? Come in.
Sean Tuohy.

01:29:58.679 --> 01:30:01.477
- Nick Saban, nice to meet you.
- Nice to see you. My pleasure.

01:30:01.649 --> 01:30:03.913
I appreciate the opportunity
to come in your home.

01:30:04.085 --> 01:30:06.519
- This is my daughter, Collins.
- Pleasure to meet you.

01:30:06.687 --> 01:30:09.554
- And you must be Leigh Anne.
- That would be me, Coach Saban.

01:30:09.724 --> 01:30:11.157
- Nice to meet you.
- You too.

01:30:11.325 --> 01:30:13.816
Just call me Nick.
This is an incredible home.

01:30:13.995 --> 01:30:16.225
The Windsor valances are a nice touch.

01:30:16.397 --> 01:30:20.390
Well, thank you.
You obviously have excellent taste.

01:30:20.568 --> 01:30:22.502
Well, we appreciate quality...

01:30:22.670 --> 01:30:24.535
...and recognize it when we see it.

01:30:26.107 --> 01:30:28.507
Michael, why don't you come in
and say hello?

01:30:28.676 --> 01:30:31.008
- Nick Saban. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

01:30:31.178 --> 01:30:33.271
And you must be SJ.
- That's me.

01:30:33.447 --> 01:30:36.848
Michael, why don't you and Nick
go into the living room and talk?

01:30:37.184 --> 01:30:38.310
Can SJ come?

01:30:38.486 --> 01:30:41.512
- Absolutely. We'll recruit the both of you.
- All right.

01:30:44.525 --> 01:30:46.686
I find him extremely handsome.

01:30:46.861 --> 01:30:48.761
Yeah, I'm right here, Leigh Anne.

01:30:48.929 --> 01:30:50.453
Yeah, I know.

01:30:50.631 --> 01:30:53.623
So, Michael, we would love
to get you down to LSU for a visit.

01:30:53.801 --> 01:30:55.769
We've got a great thing going
right now.

01:30:55.936 --> 01:30:59.394
You have an opportunity to be
successful as a person, as a student...

01:30:59.573 --> 01:31:03.805
...and an opportunity to be a part of the
next national championship team at LSU.

01:31:03.978 --> 01:31:07.004
So, what do you say?
Would you like to commit to a visit?

01:31:07.181 --> 01:31:08.614
Can I ask a question?
Sure.

01:31:08.949 --> 01:31:12.476
My brother and I are very close,
and so...

01:31:12.653 --> 01:31:17.488
...I'm very afraid that if he goes off
to school, I might not get to see him.

01:31:17.658 --> 01:31:19.319
- So...
- Go on.

01:31:19.493 --> 01:31:23.293
I guess I was just wondering
how much access I'd have to him.

01:31:23.464 --> 01:31:25.898
Well, SJ, you would have
total access to Michael.

01:31:26.067 --> 01:31:29.161
But better than that, in his first game
in Tiger Stadium...

01:31:29.336 --> 01:31:32.100
...we would like for you to lead
the team out of the tunnel.

01:31:32.273 --> 01:31:34.673
- What do you think about that?
- Sounds good.

01:31:49.156 --> 01:31:50.350
Come on in.

01:31:50.524 --> 01:31:53.721
Greetings. I'm Lou Holtz from
the University of South Carolina.

01:31:53.894 --> 01:31:56.863
Leigh Anne Tuohy. Nice to meet you.
Come on in. Michael?

01:31:57.031 --> 01:31:59.158
Hello. I'm Tommy Tuberville,
Auburn University.

01:31:59.333 --> 01:32:01.528
Leigh Anne Tuohy. Nice to meet you.
Michael?

01:32:01.702 --> 01:32:05.160
- Houston Nutt, University of Arkansas.
- Leigh Anne Tuohy. Nice to meet you.

01:32:05.339 --> 01:32:07.864
- Ole Miss cup, huh?
- Michael?

01:32:10.044 --> 01:32:12.308
Oh, come on. You know this.

01:32:12.480 --> 01:32:14.209
It's logical.

01:32:25.459 --> 01:32:28.019
I guarantee, you come to
University of South Carolina...

01:32:28.195 --> 01:32:30.686
...it'll be the smartest decision
you've ever made.

01:32:30.865 --> 01:32:34.494
We want you, we need you,
but the other thing is, Mike, you need us.

01:32:38.239 --> 01:32:39.263
Ow!

01:32:39.440 --> 01:32:42.375
Knoxville is a tremendous place
to live and-

01:32:42.543 --> 01:32:45.535
I know there's Lions,
there's Tigers, there's Bears.

01:32:45.713 --> 01:32:47.840
Hey, there's only one Razorback
in the world.

01:32:48.015 --> 01:32:51.746
And not only that, you will look great
in Gamecock red.

01:32:51.919 --> 01:32:52.943
What's in it for me?

01:32:53.120 --> 01:32:56.817
SJ, I'm gonna get you a hog hat
and the whole family a hog hat.

01:32:56.991 --> 01:32:59.118
Are you telling me that’s
the best you can do?

01:32:59.293 --> 01:33:01.591
SJ, you remind me of me as a boy.

01:33:01.762 --> 01:33:04.128
Coach, help me help you.

01:33:04.298 --> 01:33:07.825
I can give you a Gamecock headdress,
and with real feathers.

01:33:16.610 --> 01:33:20.011
- What do you got for me, Phil?
- I've been thinking a lot about that...

01:33:20.181 --> 01:33:22.775
...and one of the things
I think would be special...

01:33:22.950 --> 01:33:26.943
...is we'll walk arm-in-arm to the center
of Neyland Stadium in the first ball game...

01:33:27.121 --> 01:33:29.453
...and do the coin toss together.
How's that sound?

01:33:29.623 --> 01:33:32.091
Coach Fulmer, it's a pleasure
doing business with you.

01:33:32.259 --> 01:33:35.057
My pleasure, CJ. You bet you, buddy.

01:33:45.372 --> 01:33:46.896
Congratulations on getting hired.

01:33:47.074 --> 01:33:49.838
Thank you, ma'am.
Ole Miss is my dream job.

01:33:50.010 --> 01:33:53.138
You're coming a little late to the party
and we're diehard Rebels...

01:33:53.314 --> 01:33:55.748
...so I'm gonna pretty much
give you a road map.

01:33:55.916 --> 01:33:57.543
- Got it.
- LSU is out.

01:33:57.718 --> 01:33:59.709
Everybody knows Saban's
going to the NFL.

01:33:59.887 --> 01:34:02.685
Don't wanna name names,
but on Michael’s first two trips...

01:34:02.856 --> 01:34:05.120
- ...somebody took him to a titty bar.
- Terrible.

01:34:05.292 --> 01:34:07.487
Tell me about it.
He had nightmares for weeks.

01:34:07.661 --> 01:34:09.959
So when he visits,
I want you to feed him Italian.

01:34:10.130 --> 01:34:12.724
He likes fettuccine Alfredo.
And take him to a movie.

01:34:12.900 --> 01:34:16.131
<i>Not Chainsaw Massacre
because he’ll just cover his eyes.</i>

01:34:16.303 --> 01:34:18.703
Then get him in bed by 10. Got it?

01:34:18.872 --> 01:34:20.066
- Yes, ma'am.
- All right.

01:34:20.241 --> 01:34:22.072
- What about Tennessee?
- Mm.

01:34:22.409 --> 01:34:24.240
Breaks my heart,
but they're still in the hunt.

01:34:24.411 --> 01:34:26.777
Ahem. Fulmer made SJ a sweet deal.

01:34:26.947 --> 01:34:29.507
- I hear that kid can really pepper the gumbo.
- Hmm.

01:34:29.683 --> 01:34:32.413
He's his daddy's boy. You ready?

01:34:32.586 --> 01:34:34.486
- Let's do it.
- All right.

01:34:34.655 --> 01:34:37.089
Mike, do you love barbecue?
I tell you what, Mike.

01:34:37.258 --> 01:34:40.716
You can go to a gas station and
get the best barbecue you ever got.

01:34:40.894 --> 01:34:42.361
It's a wonderful place to live.

01:34:42.529 --> 01:34:46.693
Fried catfish, all the good food that
we love to eat and that's not good for us...

01:34:46.867 --> 01:34:49.131
...you can have it there, Mike,
I promise you.

01:34:49.303 --> 01:34:51.601
And for you, SJ, this is what I can do.

01:34:51.772 --> 01:34:53.865
At Ole Miss, we have
The Grove by the stadium.

01:34:54.041 --> 01:34:57.442
We walk it before every game
in front of thousands of people.

01:34:57.611 --> 01:34:59.511
It's a sacred ritual. And I'm in front.

01:35:00.047 --> 01:35:01.947
Seen it a thousand times.

01:35:02.116 --> 01:35:05.882
Ever seen it from the front of the line?
Next year, you and me, leading the team.

01:35:06.053 --> 01:35:09.989
Tennessee offered to let me
run on the field and flip the coin.

01:35:12.926 --> 01:35:14.985
I'll throw in a sideline pass.

01:35:25.272 --> 01:35:26.705
Have you decided yet, Michael?

01:35:27.474 --> 01:35:29.374
No, Miss Sue.

01:35:30.144 --> 01:35:32.510
But you like Tennessee?

01:35:33.480 --> 01:35:34.811
Yeah. That's a good school.

01:35:35.916 --> 01:35:37.907
Not at the academic level of Ole Miss...

01:35:38.085 --> 01:35:41.077
...but they have a outstanding
Science Department.

01:35:41.955 --> 01:35:44.185
You know what they're famous for?

01:35:44.625 --> 01:35:46.889
They work with the FBI...

01:35:47.061 --> 01:35:51.020
...to study the effects of soil
on decomposing body parts.

01:35:51.198 --> 01:35:52.893
What's that mean?

01:35:53.067 --> 01:35:56.525
Well, when they find a body, the police
wanna know how long it's been dead.

01:35:56.704 --> 01:35:59.639
So the fine folks at Tennessee
help them out.

01:36:00.441 --> 01:36:03.137
Oh, they have lots of body parts.

01:36:03.344 --> 01:36:07.405
Arms and legs and hands...

01:36:07.581 --> 01:36:10.106
...from hospitals and medical schools.

01:36:12.886 --> 01:36:14.751
And do you know where they store them?

01:36:18.692 --> 01:36:20.853
Right underneath the football field.

01:36:23.030 --> 01:36:27.558
So while it's fine and dandy
to have 100,000 fans cheering for you...

01:36:27.735 --> 01:36:32.365
...the bodies you should be worried about
are the ones right under the turf.

01:36:32.539 --> 01:36:35.633
Set to poke up through the ground
and grab you.

01:36:40.447 --> 01:36:43.416
Well, it's your decision
where you wanna play ball.

01:36:43.584 --> 01:36:45.779
Don't let me influence you.

01:37:14.448 --> 01:37:17.713
All the other teachers are on board.
I don't know what your problem is.

01:37:17.885 --> 01:37:21.821
I'm sorry. I will not give a student
a grade he or she doesn't deserve.

01:37:22.122 --> 01:37:25.455
Well, Michael needs a B.

01:37:25.626 --> 01:37:28.288
What does he have to do
to deserve that?

01:37:29.963 --> 01:37:32.830
Right now Michael’s doing
C- minus, D-plus work.

01:37:33.400 --> 01:37:37.166
His best chance at improvement is
the written essay at the end of the year.

01:37:37.337 --> 01:37:39.430
It counts for a third of the grade.

01:37:40.808 --> 01:37:43.470
Well, that's it. We're sunk.

01:37:44.845 --> 01:37:47.712
<i>Why don't you write about
Great Expectations?</i>

01:37:47.881 --> 01:37:49.746
You're a lot like Pip.

01:37:49.917 --> 01:37:55.378
I mean, he was poor. He was an orphan
and someone kind of found him.

01:37:55.556 --> 01:37:57.456
You should be able to relate to that.

01:38:01.528 --> 01:38:04.588
Fine. We'll go through the reading list.

01:38:04.765 --> 01:38:07.461
But you're gonna have to pick one,
Michael.

01:38:07.901 --> 01:38:08.925
<i>Pygmalion.</i>

01:38:12.372 --> 01:38:14.203
<i>A Tale of Two Cities.</i>

01:38:14.374 --> 01:38:16.239
"The Charge of the Light Brigade."

01:38:16.410 --> 01:38:19.846
<i>Half a league, half a league
Half a league onward</i>

01:38:20.013 --> 01:38:21.571
I love that one.

01:38:21.949 --> 01:38:24.213
He loves it.

01:38:25.886 --> 01:38:29.344
Why don't you do this?
And I'll watch basketball.

01:38:33.093 --> 01:38:34.492
Okay.

01:38:38.098 --> 01:38:41.727
<i>All in the valley of Death
Rode the six hundred.</i>

01:38:42.569 --> 01:38:46.528
They named LSU's stadium Death Valley
because of this story.

01:38:47.608 --> 01:38:51.169
Alfred, Lord Tennyson
was writing about LSU-Ole Miss.

01:38:51.345 --> 01:38:52.676
- You're kidding.
- No.

01:38:52.846 --> 01:38:55.940
- It's a great story.
- It's a poem!

01:38:56.116 --> 01:38:58.584
<i>"Forward, the Light Brigade!"</i>

01:38:58.752 --> 01:39:00.083
That's like the offense.

01:39:00.254 --> 01:39:02.381
<i>"Charge for the guns," he said:</i>

01:39:02.556 --> 01:39:03.750
It's the end zone.

01:39:04.291 --> 01:39:06.691
<i>Into the valley of Death
Rode the six hundred.</i>

01:39:06.860 --> 01:39:10.591
<i>"Forward, the Light Brigade!"
Was there a man dismay'd?</i>

01:39:11.331 --> 01:39:14.664
<i>Not tho' the soldier knew
Someone had blunder'd:</i>

01:39:14.835 --> 01:39:16.359
Someone made a mistake?

01:39:16.937 --> 01:39:19.405
Yeah. Their leader.

01:39:19.706 --> 01:39:20.934
Their coach.

01:39:22.910 --> 01:39:27.040
But why would they go ahead
if they knew he messed up?

01:39:29.683 --> 01:39:32.117
<i>Theirs not to make reply</i>

01:39:32.452 --> 01:39:35.148
<i>Theirs not to reason why</i>

01:39:35.522 --> 01:39:37.956
<i>Theirs but to do and die:</i>

01:39:38.692 --> 01:39:41.661
<i>Into the valley of Death
Rode the six hundred.</i>

01:39:44.464 --> 01:39:46.159
They're all gonna die, aren't they?

01:39:48.468 --> 01:39:49.492
Yeah.

01:39:53.040 --> 01:39:55.736
That's really, really sad.

01:39:58.912 --> 01:40:01.745
I think you just found
something to write about, Michael.

01:40:18.131 --> 01:40:20.599
<i>Courage is a hard thing to figure.</i>

01:40:20.767 --> 01:40:24.635
<i>You can have courage based
on a dumb idea or a mistake...</i>

01:40:24.805 --> 01:40:27.103
<i>...but you're not supposed to
question adults...</i>

01:40:27.274 --> 01:40:31.506
<i>...or your coach or your teacher
because they make the rules.</i>

01:40:32.479 --> 01:40:36.176
<i>Maybe they know best,
but maybe they don't.</i>

01:40:37.250 --> 01:40:41.277
<i>It all depends on who you are,
where you come from.</i>

01:40:41.455 --> 01:40:44.322
<i>Didn't at least one of the 600 guys
think about giving up...</i>

01:40:44.491 --> 01:40:46.721
<i>...and joining with the other side?</i>

01:40:46.893 --> 01:40:50.727
<i>I mean, valley of Death,
that's pretty salty stuff.</i>

01:40:53.166 --> 01:40:54.963
<i>That's why courage is tricky.</i>

01:40:56.003 --> 01:40:59.370
<i>Should you always do
what others tell you to do?</i>

01:41:00.007 --> 01:41:03.170
<i>Sometimes you might not even know
why you're doing something.</i>

01:41:03.343 --> 01:41:06.039
<i>I mean, any fool can have courage.</i>

01:41:06.847 --> 01:41:10.840
<i>But honor, that's the real reason
you either do something or you don't.</i>

01:41:11.418 --> 01:41:14.353
<i>It's who you are
and maybe who you want to be.</i>

01:41:15.756 --> 01:41:17.917
<i>If you die trying for
something important...</i>

01:41:18.091 --> 01:41:22.551
<i>...then you have both honor and
courage, and that's pretty good.</i>

01:41:23.130 --> 01:41:25.428
<i>I think that's what the writer was saying.</i>

01:41:25.599 --> 01:41:29.433
<i>That you should hope for courage
and try for honor.</i>

01:41:29.603 --> 01:41:35.166
<i>And maybe even pray that the people
telling you what to do have some too.</i>

01:41:39.212 --> 01:41:40.873
Kevin Lin.

01:41:45.919 --> 01:41:48.820
- Good job.
- Excuse me. Excuse me. Excuse me.

01:41:50.157 --> 01:41:53.092
Matthew Nichols.

01:41:53.760 --> 01:41:56.695
- 2.52.
- Hmm?

01:41:56.897 --> 01:42:01.129
Michael’s final GPA.
Got it off of Paul’s computer.

01:42:01.334 --> 01:42:03.393
He did it, Sean. He did it.

01:42:04.104 --> 01:42:06.402
Wait a minute. You broke into
the principal’s computer?

01:42:06.573 --> 01:42:08.040
Hmm?

01:42:09.109 --> 01:42:10.872
Michael Oher.

01:42:15.182 --> 01:42:17.013
Michael.

01:42:17.918 --> 01:42:20.614
Where in the world did you find
a baby picture of Michael?

01:42:20.787 --> 01:42:23.722
Scanned it off an Internet ad
for a toddler boutique.

01:42:30.097 --> 01:42:32.861
- Congratulations, Michael.
Thank you.

01:42:48.415 --> 01:42:49.848
Michael, up top!

01:42:53.286 --> 01:42:54.753
Way to go, bro.

01:42:55.422 --> 01:42:56.855
All right, that's enough.

01:42:57.023 --> 01:43:00.481
Young man, I think I need a proper hug.

01:43:05.966 --> 01:43:08.434
You're gonna be staying
in Deaton Hall. Where is it?

01:43:08.602 --> 01:43:09.899
It's 109. It's right there.

